When there is no money, we keep a pig. When we have money, we keep a dog.
When there is no money, we are content with wild herbs collected in the mountains. When we have money, we order wild herbs as delicacies in expensive restaurants.
When there is no money, we ride a bike. When we have money, we pedal an exercise bike installed in the living room.
When there is no money, we dream of getting married. When we have money, we dream of divorce.
When there is no money, the wife goes to work as a secretary. When there is money, the secretary starts working as a wife.
When there is no money, we pretend that we have it. When we have money, we pretend that we don't have it.
